author: The Press-Enterprise
title: AREA COLLEGES: Eagles soccer defeats Cuyamaca
text:
news service reports
Published: Oct. 20, 2015 Updated: 11:07 p.m. The Mt. San Jacinto women’s soccer team defeated Cuyamaca, 2-0, on the road Wednesday in a Pacific Coast Athletic Conference match.
McKayla Collins opened the scoring with a goal in the 15th minute for the Eagles (11-2, 6-1) on an assist by Ivana Hernandez.
Ryane McDevitt scored in the 68th minute with help from Kerah Hilkey.
Goalkeeper Gabriella Harley finished with one save after filling in for Riley Ludwig in the second half.
MEN’S GOLF
Otter Invitational: CSUSB’s Taylor Hood tied for first place with a 67, but fell to Nova Southeastern’s Richard Mansell in a playoff with a birdie on the par-4, 535-yard No. 1.
The Coyotes finished in fifth place with a three-round score of 883.
Bill Cullum Invitational: UC Riverside finished in ninth place, 22 shots behind Loyola Marymount, which shot a five under 283 to claim the title.
Matt Lutz (T26) and Sam Gillis (T29) were the top finishers for Highlanders after three rounds.
MEN’S SOCCER
SBVC 1, Taft 1: Robert Montes scored the lone goal for the Wolverines (5-4-7) in a nonconference game against the host Cougars (9-4-2).
Chaffey 1, Rio Hondo 1: Jose Nuno netted the game-tying goal for the Panthers (11-1-3, 2-0-1) in a Foothill Conference match against the hosting Roadrunners (10-1-4, 0-1-2).
Edgar Cervantes and Adrian Moreno each picked up an assist and Ben Galeana finished with seven saves.
WOMEN’S SOCCER
Chaffey 1, Rio Hondo 1: Rebecca Adams scored the only goal for the Panthers (10-1-2, 2-0-1 Foothill) in their tie against the host Roadrunners (9-1-3, 1-1-1).
WOMEN’S VOLLEYBALL
Pomona-Pitzer 3, Redlands 0: The Bulldogs (5-16, 1-10 SCIAC) fell 26-24, 25-16, 25-16, to the host Sagehens (10-11, 5-6).
Kiersten Langerud and Marisa Gile led the Redlands offense with nine kills apiece and Ellie McLeod registered 29 assists. Abby Hickman tallied 15 digs.
